<subSubSection id="C31F2DDDBF28FFD67D37FCE0FBD9D929" pageId="31" pageNumber="442" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BBA7E56BF28FFD67D37FCE0FBD9D929" blockId="31.[811,1399,803,1228]" pageId="31" pageNumber="442">
It has been suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF28FFD67AC9FCE0FAADDE97" box="[1234,1398,880,913]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Canis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="31" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ekloni">Canis ekloni</taxonomicName>
from northern 
<collectingRegion id="49C1B0B4BF28FFD67A1AFC07FB97DEBE" box="[1025,1100,919,952]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="31" pageNumber="442">Tibet</collectingRegion>
is a subspecies of the Corsac Fox. However, C. ekloni is a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0505D5BF28FFD67DF1FC7AFBACD901" authorityName="Hodgson" authorityYear="1842" box="[1002,1143,1002,1031]" class="Mammalia" family="Canidae" genus="Vulpes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Carnivora" pageId="31" pageNumber="442" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferrilata">V. ferrilata</taxonomicName>
. Four subspecies are recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
